^ a b Jarvis, Paul (21 December 2016). "Coca-Cola Buys AB InBev Out of Africa Unit for $3.2 Billion". Bloomberg News. Bloomberg. Retrieved 1 February 2017. Coca-Cola Co. will pay $3.15 billion to buy Anheuser-Busch InBev NV out of an African bottling joint venture ... Coca-Cola also agreed to buy AB InBev’s interest in bottling operations in Zambia, Zimbabwe, Botswana, Swaziland, Lesotho, El Salvador and Honduras for an undisclosed sum. 
^ "Listings". www.ab-inbev.com. 
^ "Interbrew buys AmBev and becomes world's number one". Beverage Daily. 3 March 2004. Archived from the original on 13 February 2008. Retrieved 9 February 2008. 
^ "Carlos Brito: (Brew)master of the universe". Fortune. 
^ China Is Key To AB InBev's Asia Growth Prospects, forbes, 16 January 2015
^ "Home". ab-inbev.com. 
